<HEAD>Iranian Embassy Vandalized In Anti-Khomeini Protest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>THE HAGUE, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 50 Dutch and Iranian
protesters smashed windows and painted slogans on the Iranian
Embassy in a demonstration against Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini's
fundamentalist government, police said.
   Hague police spokesman Rob Brons said three demonstrators were
arrested during Tuesday's protest against Iran's alleged executions
of political opponents.
   Several protesters broke into an adjacent office building in an
apparent attempt to get into the embassy, Brons told The Associated
Press.
   Protesters painted ``Down with the Islamic Republic of Iran'' and
``Free Political Prisoners'' on the embassy building, he said.
   No damage estimate was immediately available.
