   Jazz pianist Dave Brubeck was listed in
critical but stable condition after a successful triple-bypass heart
operation, doctors said.
   Brubeck, 68, underwent 4{ hours of surgery at Yale-New Haven
Hospital on Tuesday and was placed in the intensive care unit,
hospital spokeswoman Cathy Zaorski said.
   She said Brubeck would remain in the hospital up to 10 days.
   Doctors had been watching Brubeck's problems with clogged
arteries for about eight years, but decided only recently that he
should undergo surgery, Brubeck's manager Russell Gloyd said.
