<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0430</SECOND>
<HEAD>Snow in Upper Midwest; Mostly Fair Elsewhere</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow fell today in the upper Midwest, where 40-mph winds hampered
visibility in the Dakotas, and along the lower Great Lakes.
   Scattered snow fell from South Dakota to eastern Nebraska and
from northern Wyoming to Montana. Snow showers and squalls occurred
in lower Michigan, northern and central Wisconsin, northern Illinois
and eastern Minnesota.
   In addition to the Dakotas, high winds cut visibility in
southeast Minnesota and northern Illinois.
   Winter storm warnings for snow, low temperatures and gusty winds
were in effect in Minnesota and Michigan, and snow squall warnings
were posted for lakes Ontario and Erie. Advisories for snow and
blowing snow were issued for Wisconsin and upper Michigan.
   Today's forecast called for scattered snow snowers from upper
Michigan to the lower Great Lakes and northern New England; rain
along the Southern California coast, becoming snow in the mountains
and the Antelope Valley; and gusty winds across the northern Plains.
   High temperatures were predicted in the teens and 20s across much
of the nation; from 10 below zero to zero in northeast Minnesota and
southwest Wyoming; in the single digits from the upper Mississippi
Valley to Wyoming and southeast Idaho; in the 30s and 40s in the
Pacific Northwest, northern California, the southern Rockies, much
of Texas, the lower Mississippi and Tennessee valleys and the
mid-Atlantic Coast; in the 50s and 60s along the coast and in the
valleys of central California and from northern Florida to South
Carolina; and in the 70s and low 80s in parts of Florida.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 35
degrees below zero at Craig, Colo., to 75 degrees at Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 32 partly cloudy; Boston 22 fair; Buffalo 18 snow;
Charleston, S.C. 57 fair; Cincinnati 16 fair; Cleveland 14 fair;
Detroit 14 windy; Miami 69 fair; New York 28 fair; Philadelphia 24
fair; Pittsburgh 12 fair; Portland, Maine 13 foggy; Washington 27
fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 04 fair; Chicago 18 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 26
fair; Denver 03 fair; Des Moines 14 windy; Indianapolis 17 fair;
Kansas City 14 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 04 fair; Nashville 23
fair; New Orleans 38 cloudy; St. Louis 20 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 19 cloudy; Anchorage 24 cloudy; Las Vegas 30
cloudy; Los Angeles 47 rain; Phoenix 43 cloudy; Salt Lake City 05
hazy; San Diego 49 partly cloudy; San Francisco 40 fair; Seattle 34
fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 16 partly cloudy; Toronto 14 partly cloudy.
