<FIRST>r a PM-Obit-Patterson     02-08 0099</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Obit-Patterson,0103</SECOND>
<HEAD>Former Connecticut Congressman James Patterson Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAMDEN, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   James Patterson, a Republican who represented
Connecticut in Congress from 1947 to 1959, has died at age 80.
   Patterson, who lived in Bethlehem, Conn., died Tuesday at Our
Lady of Lourdes Hospital here. He helped draft the National Atomic
Energy Act of 1947, which created the Atomic Energy Commission, on
which he served.
   He was defeated for re-election to Congress in 1958 by former
Waterbury Mayor John Monagan.
   Patterson owned plumbing and building supply businesses.
   Besides his wife, Jeanne, survivors include two sons and two
daughters.
</TEXT>
