<FIRST>r i AM-Italy-ArmsSeized     02-08 0190</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Italy-Arms Seized,0193</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Seize Ship Loaded With Arms Bound For Latin America</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAVONA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Italian authorities on Wednesday seized a
Danish freighter loaded with more than 200 tons of Czechoslovak arms
bound for Latin America, the Italian news agency ANSA said.
   The agency said police arrested 11 people and confiscated 5,200
cases of rifles, pistols, submachine guns and ammunition that they
valued at $8.1 million.
   The weapons were found in the holds of the Jane Star, a Danish
ship that brought the cargo from Hamburg, West Germany, to Savona,
where it was to be loaded on another undentified ship and sent to
unspecified Central and South American countries, ANSA said.
   The agency said the ship carried two manifests, one for the
countries of destination and another for Italy that listed the cargo
as machine parts.
   Italian police arrested nine members of the crew when they
boarded the ship Wednesday afternoon in this port west of Genoa on
the Ligurian coast, ANSA said. At about the same time, two men
suspected of being involved in the arms trafficking were arrested at
the airport in Genoa, it said.
