   The three major commercial television networks
appealed to national advertisers for support in relaxing regulations
that limit the amount of prime-time entertainment networks can
produce for themselves.
   The networks, facing increasing competition from cable and
independent stations, also said Tuesday they want authority to take
a financial stake in some of the shows produced for them, and share
in money the shows make in syndication after completing their
network run.
</TEXT>
