<FIRST>r f AM-Caterpillar-President     02-08 0155</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Caterpillar-President,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>Caterpillar Announces New President to Succeed Retiring Donis</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PEORIA, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Donald V. Fites, an executive vice president
at Caterpillar Inc., was named Wednesday to succeed Peter P. Donis
as president of the company.
   Fites, who has been with Caterpillar for 36 years, will take over
the position when Donis retires May 31.
   George S. Schaefer remains chairman and chief executive of
Caterpillar.
   Fites, 55, who will also become the company's chief operating
officer, joined Caterpillar in 1956. He served with Caterpillar's
sales department in Europe, Africa and the Middle East.
   Fites was director of Caterpillar Mitsubishi in Tokyo from 1971
to 1975, and president of Caterpillar Brasil in Sao Paulo, Brazil,
in 1979-81.
   He became a vice president in 1981 and in 1985, executive vice
president in charge of worldwide marketing.
   Donis, who turns 65 on May 30, will retire in accordance with the
company's normal retirement policy, Caterpillar said.
</TEXT>
