<FIRST>r f AM-Singapore-Shakey's     02-08 0163</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Singapore-Shakey's,0171</SECOND>
<HEAD>Singapore Company Buys Shakey's Pizza</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MONTEREY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An international company based in
Singapore has agreed to acquire the domestic operations of Shakey's
Pizza U.S. and the portion of Shakey's foreign operations it does
not already own, officials said Wednesday.
   Shakey's Pizza Restaurants Inc., the nation's first franchised
pizza company, sold 100 percent of the common stock of its domestic
division, Shakey's Inc., to a newly formed U.S. company controlled
by Inno-Pacific Holdings of Singapore, company officials said.
   Inno-Pacific bought a controlling interest in Shakey's
International in September 1988.
   The terms of the acquisition, which became effective Wednesday,
were not disclosed.
   Shakey's combined domestic and international sales total about
$206.5 million. About $140 million of that figure is generated by
the 221 U.S. restaurants involved in Wednesday's agreement.
   ``This is not a buyout, this is a buyin. We invest in people,''
said Inno-Pacific chairman Herman Hochstadt, who announced the
agreement during the annual convention of Shakey's franchisees in
Monterey.
